modules.description: Handles constructing and sending email messages using specific backend implementations. Operates on email records containing headers, body, and recipient information. Enables seamless switching between SMTP, SendGrid, and Mailgun providers with tailored send functions.

Provides functions to send email through Mailgun's API using a configured HTTP post mechanism. Operates on email data structures and configuration records that include API endpoints and HTTP client settings. Used to integrate email sending into applications requiring transactional or bulk email delivery via Mailgun.
